    "lists": [
      [
        {
          "text": "is the only mage that can shift and change her attack style early on in the game."
        },
        {
          "text": "The only mage heroes having more than three active abilities in a single form are, , and."
        },
        {
          "text": "Prior to her makeover, only had three active abilities. Since then, the  has been included as the first ability, and the  has been replaced as a special skill from the first ability."
        },
        {
          "text": "During the creation of 's abilities, she had four abilities; however, she was modified into a three-skill hero in a later patch."
        },
        {
          "text": "was temporarily banned from Brawl games due to her, which provided an unfair advantage to her team (ultimate ability). For that specific game style alone, her ultimate ability's CD has been increased from 8 to 30 seconds.",
          "links": [
            {
              "type": "internal",
              "page": "Brawl"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "The only heroes that employ the concept of Yin-yang are and.",
          "links": [
            {
              "text": "Yin-yang",
              "type": "interwiki",
              "wiki": "wikipedia",
              "page": "Yin and yang"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "The only heroes who employ the concept of light and dark are and."
        },
        {
          "text": "'s original role was / later swapped to / by Patch 1.6.94 or Patch 1.7.08 she was reduced to due to a lack of a support like ability and to increase her damage to make her viable as a Mid Laner",
          "links": [
            {
              "type": "internal",
              "page": "Patch 1.6.94"
            },
            {
              "type": "internal",
              "page": "Patch 1.7.08"
            },
            {
              "type": "internal",
              "page": "Mid Laner"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "is currently the only hero who bares the / role."
        },
        {
          "text": "The closest heroes who's skills are similar to / hybrid roles are, and . 's  helps her allies to a certain location while 's  and 's  gave allies speed boost however they are still labeled as  many of the players are still requesting them to be added to the  role."
        },
        {
          "text": "Because of the introduction of Magic Damage specialty in Patch 1.4.94,, , , and become abstracted from the mage role.",
          "links": [
            {
              "text": "Magic Damage",
              "type": "internal",
              "page": "Magic Damage (Specialty)"
            },
            {
              "text": "Patch 1.4.94",
              "type": "internal",
              "page": "Patch Notes 1.4.94"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "is currently the only hero who bares the / role as of Patch 1.9.64 's role was originally / but was swapped to / due to how his gamestyle is similar to that of an and although it is not mentioned it is prompted to be to be more lore accurate said to be an \"assassin\" to murder heretics by the orders of the Church of Light (see Julian Lore).",
          "links": [
            {
              "type": "internal",
              "page": "Patch 1.9.64"
            },
            {
              "text": "Julian Lore",
              "type": "internal",
              "page": "Julian",
              "anchor": "Story"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "is the only mage capable summoning a puppet in the form of the targeted enemy."
        },
        {
          "text": "(After Vexana's Revamp back in S25, her Ultimate has now been adjusted to Eternal Guard. Refer to Patch Notes 1.6.78 (Advanced Server) for more information.)",
          "links": [
            {
              "type": "internal",
              "page": "Patch Notes 1.6.78 (Advanced Server)"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
